      "answer": "Nested TLS produces paired inner/outer pending in both ylong_base and tokio_base, so this is not a ylong-specific duplicate-pending bug. In the measured wall-clock window each runtime has 32 client response pendings, 64 inner underlying-read pendings, and 64 outer SSL-read pendings. All 64 outer pendings have a same-thread/task inner pending within 50 us for both runtimes.",
